1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to St. Clair County; to further provide for
4 the compensation of the sheriff, judge of probate, revenue
5 commissioner, chair of the county commission, and members of
6 the county commission; and to repeal Act 80-195 (1980 Regular
7 Session, p. 270), Act 84-74 (1984 Regular Session, p. 106),
8 Act 92-483 (1992 Regular Session, p. 959), Act 96-412 (1996
9 Regular Session, p. 519), Act 2005-102 (2005 Regular Session),
10 Act 2013-395 (2013 Regular Session), Act 2017-89 (2017 Regular
11 Session), Act 2019-135 (2019 Regular Session), Act 2023-120
12 (2023 Regular Session), Act 2025-113 (2025 Regular Session),
13 Section 2 of Act 1855-25 (1855-1856 Regular Session), Section
14 1 of Act 2000-560 (2000 Regular Session), and Sections 2, 3,
15 and 4 of Act 2020-182 (2020 Regular Session), relating to the
16 compensation of the sheriff, revenue commissioner, judge of
17 probate, and the chair and other members of the county
18 commission.
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
20 Section 1. (a) Commencing June 1, 2026, the Sheriff of
21 St. Clair County, in addition to the compensation the sheriff
22 received on May 31, 2026, shall receive an additional expense
23 allowance in an amount that brings the sheriff's total annual
24 compensation to one hundred sixty thousand dollars ($160,000).
25 (b) Commencing January 18, 2027, the total base annual
26 salary for the sheriff shall be one hundred sixty thousand
27 dollars ($160,000), in lieu of all other expense allowances
28 and other forms of compensation.
